<br>
I'd love to be in a raiding guild.  I've been asked if I'm interested in joining by nearly every high end guild on our server (Maelin Starpyer).  I play a ton and have played my bard for over 4 years.  I'm acknowledged as very good bard on the server.<br>
<br>
So why am I not part of a good guild?  All of them want a higher level of commitment than I can give.  At a minimum, they want 50% raiding attendance.  I simply can't do that with a wife and 3 kids at home.  I can probably make 25-40% of the raids, but that's not good enough.  I could be in partial attendance even more than that, starting after the kids are in bed.<br>
<br>
It seems to me that DKP was designed to reward players based on their attendance.  Wouldn't 5-6 part time bards be better than 0-1 full time people?  I know quite a few players of other classes in my same situation.  We're not going anywhere.  I love EQ still and have no plans to leave, I simply solo, box with my 65 druid and/or beastlord, or XP in LDoN etc.<br>
<br>
I'm hoping the turnover will convince a few good guilds that they don't need the same level of RL life commitment for someone to contribute in a small way to the guild and raids...<br>
